&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maternity Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Antenatal Administration Support&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kingston Maternity Service is a popular unit caring and delivering over 5800 women every year. The Antenatal Administration support and reception team are an essential component of our service. Ensuring women have timely appointments made; queries responded to and feel welcomed when they use our service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a friendly individual with excellent communication and organisational skills, have a minimum of 2-3 years’ experience as a receptionist / customer service advisor, and have a NVQ II in reception / administration or equivalent knowledge / experience, we would like you to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good IT skills and an excellent telephone manner are vital to this role. You will be required to communicate in a professional manner with a range of professionals within the maternity team, such as midwives, obstetricians and sonographers among others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for liaising directly with our women and their relatives, managing enquiries via the telephone and in person. You will also regularly undertake general administrative and filing duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Necessary training will be provided including an orientation programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE ENSURE THAT YOU HAVE THOROUGHLY READ THE JOB DESCRIPTION AND PERSON SPECIFICATION, AND THAT YOUR SUPPORTING STATEMENT EVIDENCES THIS. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To discuss the post informally please contact Suzanne Draper 020 8934 3248.&lt;/p&gt;
